    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Placing goods in a transportation vessel such as a ship, airplane, or automobile. The concept may be extended to fixed locations such as warehouses. In general this is done in a manner that takes up the least space for economic reasons and that limits the risk of damage.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
